cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.DS

The paper proposes a new metaheuristic algorithm based on swarm intelligence and evolutionary computation to solve global optimization problems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper also mentions the use of a social animal foraging strategy model, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SI (Swarm Intelligence). The algorithm also involves parameter sensitivity analysis, which is related to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also compares the proposed algorithm with other state-of-the-art metaheuristics, which is related to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
